{"id":"262256044_The_Ramsey_number_R3_t_has_order_of_Magnitude_t2log_t","abstract":"The Ramsey number R(s, t) for positive integers s and t is the minimum integer n for which every red-blue coloring of the edges of a complete n-vertex graph induces either a red complete graph of order s or a blue complete graph of order t. This paper proves that R(3, t) is bounded below by (1 - o(1))t(2)/log t times a positive constant. Together with the known upper bound of (1 + o(1))t(2)/log t, it follows that R(3, t) has asymptotic order of magnitude t(2)/log t. (C) 1995 John Wiley & Sons, Inc.","authors":["Jeong Han Kim"],"meta":["October 1995Random Structures and Algorithms 7(3):173-207","DOI:10.1002/rsa.3240070302"],"references":["238876025_On_Heilbronn's_Triangle_Problem","237128646_A_Dense_Infinite_Sidon_Sequence","316799240_Graduate_Texts_in_Mathematics","284877584_Graph_theory_and_probability_II","274635910_Ramsey_Theory","271512783_Graph_Theory_and_Applications","267011832_Graph_Theory_and_Probability_II","267008664_Graph_Theory_With_Application","266524225_On_a_Packing_and_Covering_Problem","266410245_Recent_results_on_some_not-so-recent_hypergraph_matching_and_covering_problems","266060249_Near_Perfect_Coverings_in_Graphs_and_Hypergraphs","265638561_Martingales_Isoperimetric_inequalities_and_random_graphs","265458975_Probability","248413997_Weighted_sums_of_certain_dependent_variables","245523278_Asymptotic_lower_bounds_for_Ramsey_numbers","244418109_Asympotic_lower_bounds_for_Ramsey_functions","243038268_Some_unsolved_problems_in_graph_theory_Russian","243003124_An_Infinite_Sidon_Sequence","242429354_Ten_Lectures_on_the_Probabilistic_Method_SIAM","238381761_Certicates_for_Random_Tournaments","236736804_On_the_method_of_bounded_differences","235737428_Random_Graph","229352776_Some_Graph_Theoretic_Results_Associated_with_Ramsey's_Theorem","228057769_Probability_Inequalities_for_Sums_of_Bounded_Random_Variables","226577256_Largest_random_component_of_ak-cube","226127310_M